definition.value: An  aminopyrimidine that is pyrimidin-4-amine substituted by a methyl group at position 2 and a diphosphooxymethyl group at position 5.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-dehydroshikimic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A disaccharide derivative that is the 2''-O-glucosyl derivative of vitexin.
A methoxybenzoate that is the conjugate base of vanillic acid.
